oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: No Tomorrow In Sight - Willie Nelson performance - 1967-06-13 ; What Right Have I - Willie Nelson performance
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance of No Tomorrow In Sight, written by Willie Nelson, produced by Chet Atkins, recorded on June 13, 1967 at RCA Victor Studio in Nashville, TN, and performed by Willie Nelson (vocals), Grady Martin (guitar), Jerry Reed (guitar), Jimmy Day (steel), Junior Huskey (bass), Johnny Bush (drums), and Jerry Smith (piano). Performance of What Right Have I, written by Willie Nelson and Jerry Jericho, and performed by Willie Nelson.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Willie Nelson
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (0:00) Willie Nelson performs "No Tomorrow In Sight" / (3:12) Willie Nelson performs "What Right Have I"
